    Class Description
    AlchemyLab
    Alchemy labs produce between 400 to 500 cookies per 2 seconds.
    ArrowButton
    Button clicked by the user to modify MenuWorld settings, by increasing or decreasing its counter.
    Baby
    Babies do not produce cookies for their player but instead take away cookies from the other player.
    BottleOfMilk
    Produced by the MilkBottles Powerup .
    Building
    A building that produces cookies for its respective player.
    BuildingRow
    The rectangles in which the buildings will stay
    BuyButton
    A button that the cursors will click in order to buy an item.
    Clickable
    An object that can be clicked
    Clicker
    Simulates the cursor of the players, which clicks the cookies, buy buttons, and buildings.
    Cookie
    Each player gets their own Cookie.
    CookieGod
    The most powerful building that produces 9000 cookies every 2-3 seconds.
    CookieMonster
    CookieMonster has entered the scene! Eats up a chunk of the opponent's cookies The amount of cookies that the CookieMonster eats depends on the player's level.
    CookieRocket
    An image of a cookie rocket that will accelerate upwards, signifying the victory of the winning player!
    CookieUpgrade
    Upgrade the Player's Cookie's level, to gain more cookies per click! Plays a sparkling animation and changes the Cookie's appearance to represent an upgrade.
    CookieWorld
    Credits
    CooldownBar
    A rectangular bar which slowly shrinks vertically over time.
    DarkOverlay
    A black background with its opacity reduced to act as a dark overlay.
    Description
    An image of a description for an item that will be displayed when the simulation viewer hovers over a buy button.
    Effect
    Superclass for all Effects.
    EndWorld
    The ending screen when a player wins
    ExtraExpensiveFilament
    Powerup that makes all 3D printers for its respective player 1.5x more efficient.
    GoButton
    Clicked by user to transition from the welcome screen to the StoryWorld.
    Grandma
    Every 1-2 seconds produces 30-50 cookies.
    GrandmaRevolution
    40-60% of the opponents' Grandma objects become angry, and begin a revolution! Instead of baking cookies, they will savagely (or as savage as a Grandma can be) destroy the opponent player's cookies
    HoverArea
    Tracks the user's cursor.
    Label
    A Label class that allows you to display a textual value on screen.
    Lag
    Player's wifi becomes destabilized, and their clickers become debilitated for 3-5 seconds
    LuckyClover
    Powerup that makes all buildings output their maximum amount.
    MenuButton
    Superclass for buttons used in the menu screen, clickable by the user.
    MenuSetting
    Create a group of actors which work together to manage a setting.
    MenuWorld
    The menu screen.
    MilkBottles
    Send BottleOfMilk's to the opponent's babies, neutralizing them
    MyException
    Exception subclass to throw custom exceptions
    Player
    A player in this simulation, of which there are two.
    Portal
    Transports 3000 - 4000 cookies from the Cookie-verse every 3 seconds.
    Powerup
    Players can gain an edge on one another by purchasing subclasses of Powerup.
    PreviewActor
    Superclass for all previewers.
    PreviewClicker
    Show preview of clicker and its speed/cps
    PreviewGrandma
    Show preview of Grandma objects
    Printer3D
    Every 4 seconds prints 1800 - 2400 cookies.
    ReverseDementia
    Powerup that makes grandmas twice as efficient and calms down any angry grandmas
    Sabotage
    Sabotages are powerups which affect the opponent (target) of its activator (origin)
    Sparkle
    Visual effect for the CookieUpgrade and LuckyClover Powerups
    StartButton
    Start the simulation!
    StoryWorld
    The world with story.
    SuperSmoothMover
    A variation of an actor that maintains a precise location (using doubles for the co-ordinates instead of ints).
    WarmMits
    Warm mittens make clickers click faster (increases their production).
    WelcomeWorld
    The title screen of the simulation.

    Type of BuyButton which is used only for the win condition (i.e.
